<!--
    Chinese, Traditional — zh-TW
    Script : Traditional Chinese characters (繁體中文); LTR (mixed LTR/vertical
             in print, but Android uses horizontal LTR layout for UI strings).
    Approx.: ~25 M speakers (Taiwan, Hong Kong, Macau; global diaspora).
    Register: Standard Modern Mandarin as written in Taiwan (國語; using ROC
              orthographic conventions).  Hong Kong usage differs primarily in
              vocabulary loanwords; the Taiwan register is the wider standard.
    Android qualifier: values-zh-rTW (Android resource syntax; BCP-47 tag is
              "zh-TW").
    Notes  : Traditional characters differ substantially from Simplified (zh-CN)
             in stroke count and in some cases in meaning; this file must NOT
             be derived by automatic conversion from values-zh-rCN.  All strings
             are independently translated.
             "Binge drinking" → 酗酒 / 豪飲 — the clinical term 豪飲 is preferred
             in formal health contexts; 酗酒 carries a stronger negative
             connotation and is used colloquially.
    Source : Translated from values-de/strings.xml (German source of truth).
-->
